  "description": "Equine/Bovine/Deer Morphus table (Nightbane RPG pp. 97–98; Dark Designs pp. 130–131). Covers four-legged herbivores from cattle and horses to deer, bison, and antelope. Centaur and minotaur shapes are common. All rows instinctively get Swimming at 65% and Climbing at 30% in Morphus. In most cases, Disguise and Undercover Ops are impossible. Unless otherwise noted, kicks and head butts inflict double damage (typically 2D6 + P.S. bonus) and jump/leap kicks do triple damage; horned or antlered creatures can head-butt for 4D6 damage.",
